<H1>Connecting commands together</H1>

<P>Unix allows you to link two or more commands together
using a pipe.  The pipe takes the 
 <A HREF="cmd3.html">standard output</A> from one
command and uses it as the <A HREF="cmd3.html">standard input</A>
 to another command.

<PRE>   command1 | command2 | command3
</PRE>

<P>The | (vertical bar) character is used to represent the
pipeline connecting the commands.</P>

<P>With practise you can use pipes to create complex
commands by combining several simpler commands together.</P>

